{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse and has begun making restitution for the $25,000 embezzled. While the crime is a breach of fiduciary duty, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is grossly disproportionate to the offense. Considering the defendant's background and the partial restitution, a short-term custodial sentence of 6 months is appropriate to serve as a deterrent and punishment without permanently destroying the defendant's ability to remain productive and repay the remaining debt.",
  "verdict": 6
}
